But as that opinion arose from the supposition that it was at our own option to reject or accept the offered grace of God, this notion being exploded, tha other falls of course. Though here is a double error, for beside reaching that our gratitude for the grace first bestowed on us, and our legitimate use of that grace, are remunerated by subsequent blessings, they add also, that now grace does not operate alone in us, but only coiiperates with us.
